                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2376: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-21T19:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1919, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received August 21, 1.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Asia Banking Corporation has made a contract for a loan of $500,000 with the
                    Hupeh Provincial Government, with Central Government sanction and guarantee
                    security income of provincial mint, purpose not stated. Japanese bank claims
                    option [on] all Hupeh loans. Provincial Government considers Japanese terms too
                    high. Should the Legation approve?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
